##  Bank Management System (C++)

A simple <b>Bank Management System</b> developed in C++ using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts and File Handling. 
This project allows users to create bank accounts, deposit and withdraw money, search for an account, and display all accounts. 
The account information is stored permanently in a text file.

# Features


* Create a New Bank Account
* Deposit Money
* Withdraw Money
* Search Account by Account Number
* Display All Accounts
* Persistent Data Storage using File Handling
* Menu-Driven Console Interface

#Technologies Used

* C++
* Object-Oriented Programming (Classes & Objects)
* STL (`vector`)
* File Handling (`fstream`)
* Console Application

# Project Structure

```text
Bank-Management-System/
│
├── main.cpp        # Source Code
├── bank.txt        # Stores Account Information
└── README.md       # Project Documentation
```

# How It Works

The application loads all existing account details from *bank.txt* when it starts.

Users can perform different banking operations through a menu-driven interface.

Whenever an account is created, updated, or modified, the latest data is automatically saved back into the file.

This ensures that account information is preserved even after closing the application.


#Menu Options

```text
===== BANK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM =====

1. Create Account
2. Deposit Money
3. Withdraw Money
4. Search Account
5. Display All Accounts
6. Exit
```
