```
#File Storage

Account information is stored in a text file named:

```text
bank.txt
```
Example:

```text
101 Ashish 5000
102 Aman 12000
103 Ankit 8000
```

The file is automatically updated after every successful transaction.



# Concepts Used

* Classes & Objects
* Encapsulation
* Vectors (STL)
* File Handling (`ifstream` / `ofstream`)
* Functions
* Loops
* Conditional Statements
* Menu-Driven Programming



# Functions Implemented

| Function             | Description                                 |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `createNewAccount()` | Creates a new bank account                  |
| `deposit()`          | Deposits money into an account              |
| `withdraw()`         | Withdraws money after checking the balance  |
| `showAccount()`      | Displays details of a specific account      |
| `showAllAccounts()`  | Displays all saved accounts                 |
| `saveData()`         | Saves account information to a file         |
| `loadData()`         | Loads saved account information from a file |



# How to Run

Compile the program:

```bash
g++ bank.cpp -o bank
```

Run the executable:

```bash
./bank
```

For Windows (MinGW):

```bash
g++ main.cpp -o bank && bank.exe
```
